title: The Rosary
creator: Florence Louisa Barclay
description: Librivox recording of the The Rosary by Florence Louisa Barclay. Read by Deb Bacon-Ziegler, Christine Blachford, Betsie Bush, Robin Cotter, Pat Elder, Maria Elmvang, rachelellen, Ana Simão. “The Rosary” is a beautiful love story. Gareth Dalmain falls in love with the Honorable Jane Champion. She loves him back, but does not trust his love, as is known to be a great lover of beauty, and she - alas - is very plain. Just as she decides to trust him, she receives news that he has been blinded in a hunting accident. She wants to go visit him, but he will not receive her, as he wants only her love - not her pity. With the help of their mutual friend and doctor, she gets the position as his nurse under a presumed name, and thereby gets to know the ‘new’ Gareth. (Summary by Maria Elmvang) M4B audio book available on the LibriVox Catalog page. For more free audiobooks, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit librivox.org.

reviews.reviewbody: A love story for the time it was written.  It is simple and the characters are not to complex, but I still enjoyed it.  This is also read by real people and not a computer, so I am grateful for all the readers for their time.   Thank you to all of them.
This was a wonderful story and well read by all who contributed.  Highly recommend this one.
Christian Readers will especially enjoy the recitation of beautiful hymns and the faith of the characters.
